00:00:21.440 --> 00:00:22.880
[Amit Varma]: and even though I was a winning player,

00:00:23.080 --> 00:00:27.080
[Amit Varma]: one of the many reasons I left poker was that I felt I was engaged

00:00:27.080 --> 00:00:30.400
[Amit Varma]: in an unproductive activity that contributed nothing to the world.

00:00:30.720 --> 00:00:32.240
[Amit Varma]: Poker is a zero sum game,

00:00:32.240 --> 00:00:35.280
[Amit Varma]: even a negative sum game if one considers a rate charged by the house.

00:00:35.560 --> 00:00:39.160
[Amit Varma]: And the only way a person can win is if someone else loses.

00:00:39.560 --> 00:00:42.560
[Amit Varma]: Basically, you have to exploit the mistakes of others.

00:00:43.120 --> 00:00:44.560
[Amit Varma]: The real world is not like this.

00:00:44.560 --> 00:00:47.560
[Amit Varma]: In everything else I do, whether it's writing or podcasting

00:00:47.560 --> 00:00:51.920
[Amit Varma]: or producing journalism, I only make money if I provide value to others.

00:00:52.160 --> 00:00:53.600
[Amit Varma]: When I benefit, so do others.

00:00:53.600 --> 00:00:55.280
[Amit Varma]: It's a positive sum game.

00:00:55.280 --> 00:00:59.560
[Amit Varma]: No wonder then that gamblers are looked upon with suspicion by non gamblers.

00:00:59.880 --> 00:01:02.280
[Amit Varma]: Not that there's anything morally wrong with gambling,

00:01:02.280 --> 00:01:04.320
[Amit Varma]: for even the losers are consenting adults.

00:01:04.640 --> 00:01:08.160
[Amit Varma]: But it's true that a poker player doesn't make the world a better place

00:01:08.160 --> 00:01:09.560
[Amit Varma]: by playing poker.

00:01:09.560 --> 00:01:12.760
[Amit Varma]: Now, there are many things in common with the world of gambling

00:01:12.760 --> 00:01:14.000
[Amit Varma]: in the world of finance,

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:17.680
[Amit Varma]: and many people view finance professionals in the same way,

00:01:18.080 --> 00:01:21.840
[Amit Varma]: as if they are just gamblers in a giant casino, creating nothing of value

00:01:21.920 --> 00:01:24.200
[Amit Varma]: and often bringing the rest of the world crashing down,

00:01:24.200 --> 00:01:26.080
[Amit Varma]: such as when there's a financial crisis.

00:01:26.680 --> 00:01:29.240
